    "creation_date" : 1305628175,
    "answer_id" : 6029518,
    "question_id" : 6029495,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<pre><code>int min = 65;\nint max = 80;\n\nRandom r = new Random();\nint i1 = r.nextInt(max - min + 1) + min;\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>Note that <code>nextInt(int max)</code> returns an <code>int</code> between 0 inclusive and max exclusive. Hence the <code>+1</code>.</p>\n"
